properties.headline: Wind Chill Warning issued January 14 at 3:24AM AKST until January 16 at 10:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Dangerously cold wind chills. Wind chills of 55 to 65
below zero.

* WHERE...Klondike Highway near White Pass.

* WHEN...Until 10 AM AKST Thursday. Worst conditions during the
overnight and early morning hours.

* IMPACTS...The dangerously cold wind chills could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 5 to 10 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Near Skagway, wind chills of as low as 30
below zero expected.
properties.instruction:
A warning means that deadly wind chill temperatures are already
occurring or imminent.

Avoid outside activities if possible. When outside, make sure you
wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM AKST THURSDAY FOR WHITE PASS
